SUMMARY:Historic Little India: Gerrard India Bazaar (REVISED FOR 2026)
DESCRIPTION:Toronto History Walks\n\\*\\***The Toronto History Walks Explo
 rer Pass is available. Get it now for $125.00 for 1 year of unlimited tour
 s\, email**\n**torontohistorywalks@gmail.com**\n**for more information or 
 for signing up!\\*\\***\n\n\\*\\* **Please note: Please e-transfer the Tic
 ket amount when booking your space for this tour! You can e-transfer to th
 e following email at:**\n**torontohistorywalks@gmail.com**\n\nThe story of
  historic Little India is a true Toronto success story\, a unique look at 
 a neighbourhood and the people who call it home. But the story is not alwa
 ys a happy one. Like all other areas in Toronto\, Little India started out
  as a purely English - Anglican area and was repeatedly changed as other i
 mmigrants opted to leave the security of the downtown core for outer areas
 .\n\nWith the opening of the Naaz theatre in 1972\, the community that bec
 ame Little India started to take shape\, but in Toronto the forces that de
 veloped communities were different in that part of the city sandwiched bet
 ween Leslieville to the south\, and Greektown to the north.\n\nWith a stri
 ctly Anglo-Saxon pro-British community entrenched for over 100 years\, now
  changing to include south Asians\, the area was seen as a rather depresse
 d area\, or an area in transition\, and violence was an unfortunate part o
 f life. Racial tensions increased dramatically with the influx of south As
 ians.\n\nBut by the 1980s and 1990s the district had found its feet\, and 
 Little India was a popular Toronto district and tourist attraction\, with 
 visitors pouring in from around the world to partake of the richness. A tr
 ue cultural enclave in Toronto! A fascinating history and a fascinating co
 mmunity awaits! This tour has been revised a few times to add more histori
 c information to the walk\, it has been revised once again for 2026 with n
 ew landmarks and stories attached. Should be a fascinating walk!\n\nThis w
 alk is for all fitness levels. The meeting place for our walking adventure
  is on the southwest corner of Greenwood Avenue and Gerrard Street East!\n
 \nThis tour has a ticket price of $15.00 per person!\n\n\\*\\* **Please no
 te: Please e-transfer the Ticket amount when booking your space for this t
 our! You can e-transfer to the following email at:**\n**torontohistorywalk
 s@gmail.com**
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/the-history-of-parkdale/events/313034
 609/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260124T124743Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260124T124743Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Meetup: History of Parkdale
UID:event_313367250@meetup.com
